panels.description: Mean over 10s of Data Rate (expressed as packets per second, p/s) by pacman. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow/Red threasholds = 30k/300k packets/s. The Data Rate sent to InfluxDB is sent by IO_channel. To get the Data Rate for the full tile we have to sum all of the 32 IO_channels in a particular pacman. To get the 10s mean we sum all of the IO_channels over a 10 second period and then divide by 10.
panels.title: Data Rate by Pacman (10s mean)

panels.description: Configuration Rate: mean over 10s interval. Config packets should only appear while configuring ADCs. In a normal run mode, the appearance of configuration packets indicates a problem, such as a misconfigured chip or bits that flipped in transmission. Y-axis is log base 2. Thresholds are set for normal run mode as Yellow / Red = .1 p/s / .2 p/s
panels.title: Configuration Rate  by Pacman (10s mean)

panels.description: FIFO > 1/2 (or Full) is the fraction of times the FIFO was more than half full (or Full) divided by the total number of observations over a 10s window. "Shared" FIFO is calculated at the chip level. This graph shows the mean chip level ratio for the entire system. This stacked bar chart shows the FIFO > 1/2 (but not completely full) as a blue bar. On top of the blue bar is FIFO full shown as a red bar. Yellow / Red Thresholds are 0.1 / 0.2
panels.title: Shared FIFO > 1/2 and Full - System (10s means)

panels.description: The green bars are centered at the 10s Mean ADC values. The top/bottom of each bar is at mean +/- RMS. Mean and RMS values are calculated as the Mean of ten 1s mean ADC Values. Yellow / Red Thresholds = 250 / 254
panels.title: ADC Mean and RMS - System (10s mean)

panels.description: Temps > 90C will shut processor down
panels.title: Processor Temperatures

panels.description: Each pacman should acknowledge reception of a 1Hz sync signal. Missing acknowledgements in particular Pacmen may indicate a problem in those pacmen. If the signal is missing from all Pacmen it may indicate a problem with the sync pulse transmission.
panels.title: Sync Pulse

panels.description: Histogram shows distribution of Chip-level ADC 10s mean values over the global time window. The bucket size is 1. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the signal maxed out. Consistent 255 values (or consistent values below 5) may mean the threshold is set too high (or too low). Both problematic threshold cases could result in missing information.
panels.title: ADC Mean Distribution - Chip-level data (1s Means)

panels.description: Configuration Rate: mean over 10s interval. Config packets should only appear while configuring ADCs. In a normal run mode, the appearance of configuration packets indicates a problem, such as a misconfigured chip or bits that flipped in transmission. Y-axis is log base 2. Thresholds are set for normal run mode as Yellow / Red = .1 p/s / .2 p/s
panels.title: Configuration Rate  by Pacman (10s mean)

panels.description: FIFO > 1/2 (or Full) is the fraction of times the FIFO was more than half full (or Full) divided by the total number of observations over a 10s window. "Shared" FIFO is calculated at the chip level. This graph shows the mean chip level ratio for the entire system. This stacked bar chart shows the FIFO > 1/2 (but not completely full) as a blue bar. On top of the blue bar is FIFO full shown as a red bar. Yellow / Red Thresholds are 0.1 / 0.2
panels.title: Shared FIFO > 1/2 and Full - System (10s means)

panels.description: Invalid parity indicates that bits flipped at some point in the packet's transmission from chip to pacman. Invalid Parity % = sum (invalid parity) / sum (total) for each 10s interval over entire system. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow threshold is 1%, Red threshold is 10%.
panels.title: Invalid Parity Rate - System (10s mean)

panels.description: These boxes check to see if VDDD and IDDD are within threshold ranges. Digital voltage (VDDD) is supplied to digital side of ADC to power data transfer to and from chips. Acceptable range is (1.5 to 1.8V) for all pacmen except P5-P6 whose acceptable range is (1.1 to 1.3V) - the exception is needed because of differences between versions of the chips used (V2A versus V2B). Similarly IDDD is current supplied to the digital side. Thresholds are 350-750mA for all pacmen.
panels.title: Power Alerts: Are VDDD and IDDD within Threshold

panels.description: Any chip numbered outside of the range  (11, 110) is invalid and indicates corrupted data. This table  sorts data rates by chip number. Thresholds are < 11 or > 110
panels.title: Highest Chip #'s

panels.description: Any chip outside of the range  (11, 110) is invalid and indicates corrupted data. This table sorts data rates by chip #, ordering the lowest values on top.
panels.title: Lowest Chip #'s

panels.description: Highest 100 pixel data rates (expressed as # packets per second) in a given pacman. Each value is  mean rate over the last 10s. Yellow/Red thresholds = 1 / 5 p/s
panels.title: TOP-100 PIXEL DATA RATES by Pacman (over last 1m)

panels.description: These are the highest 100 ADC 10s mean values recorded over the last 30s. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the ADC maxed out, which could mean we're missing information. This could require an expert to reset the threshold.  Yellow / Red thresholds = 250 / 254
panels.title: TOP-100 PIXEL ADC MEAN (10s) BY PACMAN OVER LAST 30s

panels.description: Green bars are centered at Chip-level Mean ADC value, the top/bottom of the bars are at Mean +/- RMS. All values are calculated over a 10s window.  Red / Yellow thresholds at 250 / 254
panels.title: ADC MEAN and RMS CANDLESTICKS BY PACMAN - Chip-level data (10s Mean)

panels.description: Histogram shows distribution of Chip-level ADC 10s mean values over the global time window. The bucket size is 1. ADC values are recorded using 8 bits. A value of 255 indicates the signal maxed out. Consistent 255 values (or consistent values below 5) may mean the threshold is set too high (or too low). Both problematic threshold cases could result in missing information.
panels.title: ADC 10s MEAN HISTOGRAM - Chip-level Data (over global time window)

panels.description: Temps > 90C will shut processor down.
panels.title: Processor Temperature

panels.description: Digital Voltage/Current (VDDD/IDDD) supplied to the digital side of the ADC powers data transfers to and from chips. Analogue Voltage/Current (VDDA/IDDA) supplied to the analogue side of the ADC powers charge collection from pixel to ADC. Thresholds for all EXCEPT P5-P6 are: VDDD (1.6-1.7V), VDDA (1.8-1.9V), IDDD (400-700mA), IDDA (150-475mA).  Thresholds differ for P5-P6 (VDDD 1.15-1.25V, IDDA 60-110mA) because the chip versions are different (V2A vs V2B).
panels.title: Voltages (VDDD - digital, VDDA - analogue), and Currents (IDDD - digital, IDDA - analogue) supplied to the Chip  - Values are recorded every 30s

panels.description: Invalid parity indicates that bits flipped at some point in the packet's transmission from chip to pacman. Invalid Parity % = sum (invalid parity) / sum (total) for each 10s interval. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow threshold is 0.0001, Red threshold is 0.001.
panels.title: Invalid Parity % by Pacman (10s mean)

panels.description: FIFO > 1/2 (or Full) is the fraction of times the FIFO was more than half full (or Full) divided by the total number of observations over a 10s window. "Shared" FIFO is calculated at the chip level. This graph shows the mean chip level ratio for Pacman 1. The stacked bars show the FIFO > 1/2 (but not completely full) as a gree bar, with the FIFO full on top of it as an orange bar. Yellow / Red thresholds are 10% / 20%
panels.title: Shared FIFO > 1/2 and FULL (10s Means)

panels.description: Configuration Rate: mean over 1s interval. Config packets should only appear while configuring ADCs. In a normal run mode, configuration packets indicate a problem, such as a misconfigured chip or bits that flipped in transmission. Y-axis is log base 2. Yellow threshold is 0.1 p/s, Red threshold is 0.2 p/s
panels.title: Configuration Rate (1s Mean) by Pacman
